Here's an idea you should waste time implementing:
There's an over-world consisting of three areas
>Cul-de-sac
>Strip Mall
>Costco
The Cul-de-sac is the home-base as well as the in-game character selection. You can adjust settings like audio and video on a cathode-ray tube television.
The Strip Mall is where you can buy boards, and all store clerks are just a 2D sprite wandering up and down the desks to sell accessories and skins for characters and boards.
And the Costco is where there is a billboard and a practice skate park.
There you can practice or take on "quests" from the billboard.
Kelly is always here performing a random task. She is also a 2D sprite.

You should do absolutely none of this, I stole the whole idea from the Ed Edd n Eddy game on PS2.
